setObjects

public void setObjects(java.lang.String mode)
Here the way how faces are grouped is specified.

"none" - the faces will not be grouped

"manual" - In this mode setObject is used to specify the group. All Shapes drawn after a setObject will be part of this group

"automatic" - not supported for now

Parameters:
mode - "none", "manual", "automatic (not supported for now)"

setMaterials

public void setMaterials(java.lang.String mode)
Here the way the materials are generated is specified.

"none" - no materials will be exported, the model will be covered with one default material

"manual" - In this mode setMaterial is used to specify the color. Its used like fill()

"automatic" - the fill() statements are used to create Materials. they are named: Mat0, Mat1, etc only usefull if you don't call stroke() in your sketch, its better to set materials manual!!

Parameters:
mode - "none", "manual", "automatic"

setMaterial

public void setMaterial(java.lang.String name,
                        int r,
                        int g,
                        int b,
                        int a)
set the Material for the following drawings, this is used like fill(), just with the possibility to specify a name

if a material with the same name already exist, this material will be used!

Parameters:
name - "a name for the Material"
r - "the red value 0-255"
g - "the green value 0-255"
b - "the blue value 0-255"
a - "the alpha value 0-255"

setMaterial

public void setMaterial(java.lang.String name,
                        int r,
                        int g,
                        int b)
set the Material for the following drawings, this is used like fill(), just with the possibility to specify a name

if a material with the same name already exist, this material will be used!

the alpha value will be set to 255

Parameters:
name - "a name for the Material"
r - "the red value 0-255"
g - "the green value 0-255"
b - "the blue value 0-255"

setMaterial

public void setMaterial(java.lang.String name)
set the Material for the following drawings, this is used like fill(), just with the possibility to specify a name

if a material with the same name already exist, this material will be used!

the color will be black - (0,0,0) the alpha value will be set to 255

Parameters:
name - "a name for the Material"
